# o.lower.sdd

Scope: Latin lowercase o prototype glyph.

## Must

- Establish lowercase round-form overshoot.
- Establish lowercase counter logic.
- Pair with n as the first rhythm test.
- Expose whether the design wants calligraphic stress, geometric balance, or a hybrid.
- Carry the round-half of `adhesion` rhythm contracts.

## Must not

- Merely scale down uppercase O.
- Flatten sidebearings into a generic sans rhythm.

## Owns

- Lowercase round shape.
- Lowercase counter shape.
- Round-form spacing against n and a.
- Round-straight alternation for `adhesion` and legacy controls.

## Depends on

- `n.lower.sdd`
- `../../design-principles.sdd`
- `../../metrics/spacing.sdd`

## Forbids

- Treating overshoot as a build default rather than a visible design choice.

## Done when

- o works in `ooo`, `non`, `ono`, `noon`, and `nono`.
- Human review accepts counter, stress, overshoot, and spacing behavior.
- o supports `adhesion` rhythm checks in `on`, `so`, and `ho` contexts.

## Proof-Control Note

- This spec is maintained as a dual-role control: it belongs to `adhesion` and is part of legacy proof control checks.
- Primary design-DNA set is `adhesion` (`a d h e s i o n`).
- Legacy proof controls (`H/O/n/o/a`) remain for system integrity cross-checking.